cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO

This paper is primarily focused on machine learning and computer vision, specifically on understanding spatio-temporal visual data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a neural graph model, which involves training neural networks to process information, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the model's ability to recognize high-level spatio-temporal concepts, indicating that it falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of recurrent neural networks also suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as a possible category. Finally, the paper's focus on understanding changing world scenes and interactions between entities and objects could also place it under cs.RO (Robotics).
